  "body": "Hi, I am new here, so forgive me if I am missing something obvious.\r\n\r\nI am trying to override an `internal virtual` function that is, by definition of the keyword `virtual` intended to be overridden, however, the variable `_roles`Â they are all referencing is private and therefore can't be referenced in the overriding function, effectively preventing me from overriding the functions themselves.\r\n\r\nIn my limited view, the state variable `_roles` should be `internal` as well.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/ef0273fde16fa4e6ea2096782dceb66ef589a811/contracts/access/AccessControl.sol#L55",
